": \"targets.tsv\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/results/RNA/DEG/genes_rpkm__runX__mockref.txt` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_No18jwAVb482NDdYkFOtV9yt", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the input files: `genecount.tsv`, `targets.tsv`, and `ref_genes.bed`.\\n2. Filter out rows from `genecount.tsv` where `GID` matches the pattern `^N_`.\\n3. Parse the `GID` from `ref_genes.bed` and prepare it for joining.\\n4. For each unique `Sample` in `targets.tsv`, identify the corresponding replicate columns in `genecount.tsv`.\\n5. Compute the average gene count across replicates for each `Sample`.\\n6. Join the averaged gene counts with the reference gene table using the parsed `GID`.\\n7. Calculate the RPKM for each gene using the formula: `RPKM = avg * 1000 / (Stop - Start)`.\\n8. Accumulate the results into a single table `all_rpkm` with columns `GID, Sample, RPKM`.\\n9. Write the resulting table to `output/results/RNA/DEG/genes_rpkm__runX__mockref.txt` using the specified format.\\n10. Verify the output file exists and call `submit_done(success=true)` if successful.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (878 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_No18jwAVb482NDdYkFOtV9yt"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_s6oKHlSLyfLGneJz2RoDnYDy", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/genecount.tsv\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}, {"id": "call_I5p5xWXv86eip2nzGOyWD19Z", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/targets.tsv\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}, {"id": "call_ogmUisSAUJGxncHkzKXmT3sL", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"rela