), `input/targets.tsv` (columns `Sample, Replicate`), and\n`input/ref_genes.bed` (headerless 6-col BED: `Chr Start Stop Name Value Strand`,\nwhere `Name` contains `ID=gene:<id>;...`).\n\nFor each genotype (unique `Sample`), take the per-replicate columns whose names\ncontain the genotype, compute `avg` across replicates, join with the reference\ngene table (on parsed `GID`), compute `RPKM = avg * 1000 / (Stop - Start)`, and\naccumulate into a single table `all_rpkm` with columns `GID, Sample, RPKM`.\nWrite it to `output/results/RNA/DEG/genes_rpkm__runX__mockref.txt` via\n`write.table(..., sep='\\t', row.names=FALSE, col.names=TRUE, quote=FALSE)`.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/results/RNA/DEG/genes_rpkm__runX__mockref.txt` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: results/RNA/DEG/genes_rpkm__runX__mockref.txt under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"genecount.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"genecount.tsv\"\n    },\n    \"ref_genes.bed\": {\n      \"_file\": \"ref_genes.bed\"\n    },\n    \"targets.tsv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"targets.tsv\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/results/RNA/DEG/genes_rpkm__runX__mockref.txt` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_No18jwAVb482NDdYkFOtV9yt", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the input files: `genecount.tsv`, `targets.tsv`, and `ref_genes.bed`.\\n2. Filter out rows from `genecount.tsv` where `GID` matches the pattern `^N_`.\\n3. Parse the `GID` from `ref_genes.bed` and prepare it for joining.\\n4. For each unique `Sample` in `targets.tsv`, identify the corresponding replicate columns in `genecount.tsv`.\\n5. Compute the average gene count across replicates for each `Sample`.\\n6. Join the averaged gene counts with the reference gene table using the parsed `GID`.\\n7. Calculate the RPKM for each gene using the formula: `RPKM = avg * 1000 / (Stop - Start)`.\\n8. Accumulate the results into a single table `all_rpkm` with columns `GID, Sample, RPKM`.\\n9. Write the resulting table to `output/results/RNA/DEG/genes_rpkm__runX__mockref.txt` using the specified format.\\n10. Verify the output file exists and call `submit_done(success=true)` if successful.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (878 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_No18jwAVb482NDdYkFOtV9yt"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_s6oKHlSLyfLGneJz2RoDnYDy", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/genecount.tsv\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}, {"id": "call_I5p5xWXv86eip2nzGOyWD19Z", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/targets.tsv\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}, {"id": "call_ogmUisSAUJGxncHkzKXmT3sL", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/ref_genes.bed\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "GID\tWT_1\tWT_2\tWT_3\tKO_1\tKO_2\tKO_3\nGENE_00000\t1314\t233\t56\t1523\t568\t506\nGENE_00001\t462\t290\t1513\t214\t1390\t1521\nGENE_00002\t1832\t1121\t183\t1214\t869\t70\nGENE_00003\t66\t196\t452\t481\t1039\t1237\nGENE_00004\t59\t1154\t412\t1471\t1335\t1441\nGENE_00005\t1121\t864\t456\t924\t1211\t574\nGENE_00006\t1662\t1785\t18\t1559\t1655\t331\nGENE_00007\t1434\t870\t701\t574\t323\t445\nGENE_00008\t1965\t1568\t694\t214\t194\t783\nGENE_00009\t203\t740\t1740\t709\t1241\t546\nGENE_00010\t1657\t93\t1499\t945\t1103\t260\nGENE_00011\t1997\t1893\t780\t166\t1135\t605\nGENE_00012\t1703\t1292\t1271\t1818\t1769\t7