 %>% \\n    select(GID, Sample=sample, RPKM)\\n  \\n  # Accumulate results\\n  all_rpkm <- bind_rows(all_rpkm, joined_data)\\n}\\n\\n# Write the result to file\\nwrite.table(all_rpkm, 'output/results/RNA/DEG/genes_rpkm__runX__mockref.txt', sep='\\\\t', row.names=FALSE, col.names=TRUE, quote=FALSE)\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\n\nAttaching package: \u2018dplyr\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:stats\u2019:\n\n    filter, lag\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    intersect, setdiff, setequal, union\n\nError in `select()`:\n! Can't select columns that don't exist.\n\u2716 Column `WT` doesn't exist.\nBacktrace:\n     \u2586\n  1. \u251c\u2500... %>% select(GID, Sample = sample, RPKM)\n  2. \u251c\u2500dplyr::select(., GID, Sample = sample, RPKM)\n  3. \u251c\u2500dplyr:::select.data.frame(., GID, Sample = sample, RPKM)\n  4. \u2502 \u2514\u2500tidyselect::eval_select(expr(c(...)), data = .data, error_call = error_call)\n  5. \u2502   \u2514\u2500tidyselect:::eval_select_impl(...)\n  6. \u2502     \u251c\u2500tidyselect:::with_subscript_errors(...)\n  7. \u2502     \u2502 \u2514\u2500base::withCallingHandlers(...)\n  8. \u2502     \u2514\u2500tidyselect:::vars_select_eval(...)\n  9. \u2502       \u2514\u2500tidyselect:::walk_data_tree(expr, data_mask, context_mask)\n 10. \u2502         \u2514\u2500tidyselect:::eval_c(expr, data_mask, context_mask)\n 11. \u2502           \u2514\u2500tidyselect:::reduce_sels(node, data_mask, context_mask, init = init)\n 12. \u2502             \u2514\u2500tidyselect:::walk_data_tree(new, data_mask, context_mask)\n 13. \u2502               \u2514\u2500tidyselect:::as_indices_sel_impl(...)\n 14. \u2502                 \u2514\u2500tidyselect:::as_indices_impl(...)\n 15. \u2502                   \u2514\u2500tidyselect:::chr_as_locations(x, vars, call = call, arg = arg)\n 16. \u2502                     \u2514\u2500vctrs::vec_as_location(...)\n 17. \u2514\u2500vctrs (local) `<fn>`()\n 18.   \u2514\u2500vctrs:::stop_subscript_oob(...)\n 19.     \u2514\u2500vctrs:::stop_subscript(...)\n 20.       \u2514\u2500rlang::abort(...)\nWarning message:\nUsing an external vector in selections was deprecated in tidyselect 1.1.0.\n\u2139 Please use `all_of()` or `any_of()` instead.\n  # Was:\n  data %>% select(sample)\n\n  # Now:\n  data %>% select(all_of(sample))\n\nSee <https://tidyselect.r-lib.org/reference/faq-external-vector.html>. \nExecution halted\n", "name": "run_rscript", "tool_call_id": "call_a2qgr7fu9Xft5Jsou2RHM8K4"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_LlnHR2xzvzvSFJZ3ZySg3jkY", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read the input files: `genecount.tsv`, `targets.tsv`, and `ref_genes.bed`.\\n2. Filter out rows from `genecount.tsv` where `GID` matches the pattern `^N_`.\\n3. Parse the `GID` from `ref_genes.bed` and prepare it for joining.\\n4. For each unique `Sample` in `targets.tsv`, identify the corresponding replicate columns in `genecount.tsv`.\\n5. Compute the average gene count across replicates for each `Sample`.\\n6. Join the averaged gene counts with the reference gene table using the parsed `GID`.\\n7. Calculate the RPKM for each gene using the formula: `RPKM = avg * 1000 / (Stop - Start)`.\\n8. Accumulate the results into a single table `all_rpkm` with columns `GID, Sample, RPKM`.\\n9. Write the resulting table to `output/results/RNA/DEG/genes_rpkm__runX__mockref.txt` using the specified format.\\n10. Verify the output file exists and call `submit_done(success=true)` if successful.\\n\\n# Issue\\nThe R script failed due to a column selection error. I will fix the column selection by using `all_of()` for dynamic column names.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "next_agent_state": {"tools": [{"type": "function", "info": {"name": "run_shell"